  "text": "Free amino acids were purified by mixing 200 μl 10% sulfosalicylic acid with 800 μl plasma to precipitate high molecular-weight proteins. The amino acids were then analyzed with an amino acid analyzer (LC 5001; Biotronik, München, Germany) by ion-exchange chromatography. The amino acids were separated by using standard lithium citrate buffers of pH 2.85, 2.89, 3.20, 4.02 and 3.49. The post column derivatization was performed with ninhydrin [CITATION_1] .",
